#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.rst:52
msgid ""
"It uses a built in list of authoritative nameservers for the root zone "
"(``.``), the so called root hints. On receiving a DNS query it will ask "
"the root nameservers for an answer and will in almost all cases receive a"
" delegation to a top level domain (TLD) authoritative nameserver. It will"
" then ask that nameserver for an answer. It will recursively continue "
"until an answer is found or no answer is available (NXDOMAIN). For "
"performance and efficiency reasons that answer is cached for a certain "
"time (the answer's time-to-live or TTL). A second query for the same name"
" will then be answered from the cache. Unbound can also do DNSSEC "
"validation."
msgstr ""

