#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3894
msgid ""
"View specific local zone elements. Has the same types and behaviour as "
"the global :ref:`local-zone:<unbound.conf.local-zone>` elements. When "
"there is at least one *local-zone:* specified and :ref:`view-first: "
"no<unbound.conf.view.view-first>`, the default local-zones will be added "
"to this view. Defaults can be disabled using the nodefault type. When "
":ref:`view-first: yes<unbound.conf.view.view-first>` or when a view does "
"not have a :ref:`local-zone:<unbound.conf.view.local-zone>`, the global "
":ref:`local-zone:<unbound.conf.local-zone>` will be used including it's "
"default zones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3909
msgid ""
"View specific local data elements. Has the same behaviour as the global "
":ref:`local-data:<unbound.conf.local-data>` elements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3916
msgid ""
"View specific local-data-ptr elements. Has the same behaviour as the "
"global :ref:`local-data-ptr:<unbound.conf.local-data-ptr>` elements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3928
msgid "view-first: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3923
msgid ""
"If enabled, it attempts to use the global :ref:`local-zone:<unbound.conf"
".local-zone>` and :ref:`local-data:<unbound.conf.local-data>` if there is"
" no match in the view specific options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3931
msgid "Python Module Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3933
msgid ""
"The **python:** clause gives the settings for the *python(1)* script "
"module. This module acts like the iterator and validator modules do, on "
"queries and answers. To enable the script module it has to be compiled "
"into the daemon, and the word ``python`` has to be put in the :ref"
":`module-config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` option (usually first, or "
"between the validator and iterator). Multiple instances of the python "
"module are supported by adding the word ``python`` more than once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3943
msgid ""
"If the :ref:`chroot:<unbound.conf.chroot>` option is enabled, you should "
"make sure Python's library directory structure is bind mounted in the new"
" root environment, see *mount(8)*. Also the :ref:`python-"
"script:<unbound.conf.python.python-script>` path should be specified as "
"an absolute path relative to the new root, or as a relative path to the "
"working directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3955
msgid "python-script: *<python file>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3953
msgid ""
"The script file to load. Repeat this option for every python module "
"instance added to the :ref:`module-config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3958
msgid "Dynamic Library Module Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3960
msgid ""
"The **dynlib:** clause gives the settings for the ``dynlib`` module. This"
" module is only a very small wrapper that allows dynamic modules to be "
"loaded on runtime instead of being compiled into the application. To "
"enable the dynlib module it has to be compiled into the daemon, and the "
"word ``dynlib`` has to be put in the :ref:`module-config:<unbound.conf"
".module-config>` attribute. Multiple instances of dynamic libraries are "
"supported by adding the word ``dynlib`` more than once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3969
msgid ""
"The :ref:`dynlib-file:<unbound.conf.dynlib.dynlib-file>` path should be "
"specified as an absolute path relative to the new path set by "
":ref:`chroot:<unbound.conf.chroot>`, or as a relative path to the working"
" directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3979
msgid "dynlib-file: *<dynlib file>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3977
msgid ""
"The dynamic library file to load. Repeat this option for every dynlib "
"module instance added to the :ref:`module-config:<unbound.conf.module-"
"config>` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3982
msgid "DNS64 Module Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3984
msgid ""
"The ``dns64`` module must be configured in the :ref:`module-"
"config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` directive, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3991
#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4169
msgid "and be compiled into the daemon to be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:3995
#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4172
#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4301
msgid "These settings go in the :ref:`server:<unbound.conf.server>` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4003
msgid "dns64-prefix: *<IPv6 prefix>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4000
msgid ""
"This sets the DNS64 prefix to use to synthesize AAAA records with. It "
"must be /96 or shorter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4003
msgid "Default: 64:ff9b::/96"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4015
msgid "dns64-synthall: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4012
msgid ""
"If enabled, synthesize all AAAA records despite the presence of actual "
"AAAA records."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4024
msgid "dns64-ignore-aaaa: *<domain name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4020
msgid ""
"List domain for which the AAAA records are ignored and the A record is "
"used by DNS64 processing instead. Can be entered multiple times, list a "
"new domain for which it applies, one per line. Applies also to names "
"underneath the name given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4027
msgid "NAT64 Operation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4029
msgid ""
"NAT64 operation allows using a NAT64 prefix for outbound requests to "
"IPv4-only servers. It is controlled by two options in the "
":ref:`server:<unbound.conf.server>` section:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4041
msgid "do-nat64: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4037
msgid ""
"Use NAT64 to reach IPv4-only servers. Consider also enabling :ref"
":`prefer-ip6:<unbound.conf.prefer-ip6>` to prefer native IPv6 connections"
" to nameservers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4049
msgid "nat64-prefix: *<IPv6 prefix>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4046
msgid ""
"Use a specific NAT64 prefix to reach IPv4-only servers. The prefix length"
" must be one of /32, /40, /48, /56, /64 or /96."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4049
msgid ""
"Default: 64:ff9b::/96 (same as "
":ref:`dns64-prefix:<unbound.conf.dns64.dns64-prefix>`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4052
msgid "DNSCrypt Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4054
msgid ""
"The **dnscrypt:** clause gives the settings of the dnscrypt channel. "
"While those options are available, they are only meaningful if Unbound "
"was compiled with ``--enable-dnscrypt``. Currently certificate and "
"secret/public keys cannot be generated by Unbound. You can use dnscrypt-"
"wrapper to generate those: https://github.com/cofyc/dnscrypt-"
"wrapper/blob/master/README.md#usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4067
msgid "dnscrypt-enable: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4064
msgid ""
"Whether or not the dnscrypt config should be enabled. You may define "
"configuration but not activate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4076
msgid "dnscrypt-port: *<port number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4072
msgid "On which port should dnscrypt should be activated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4075
msgid ""
"There should be a matching interface option defined in the "
":ref:`server:<unbound.conf.server>` section for this port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4083
msgid "dnscrypt-provider: *<provider name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4081
msgid ""
"The provider name to use to distribute certificates. This is of the form:"
" ``2.dnscrypt-cert.example.com.``. The name *MUST* end with a dot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4089
msgid "dnscrypt-secret-key: *<path to secret key file>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4088
msgid ""
"Path to the time limited secret key file. This option may be specified "
"multiple times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4096
msgid "dnscrypt-provider-cert: *<path to cert file>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4094
msgid ""
"Path to the certificate related to the :ref:`dnscrypt-secret-"
"key:<unbound.conf.dnscrypt.dnscrypt-secret-key>`. This option may be "
"specified multiple times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4117
msgid "dnscrypt-provider-cert-rotated: *<path to cert file>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4101
msgid ""
"Path to a certificate that we should be able to serve existing connection"
" from but do not want to advertise over :ref:`dnscrypt-"
"provider:<unbound.conf.dnscrypt.dnscrypt-provider>` 's TXT record certs "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4106
msgid ""
"A typical use case is when rotating certificates, existing clients may "
"still use the client magic from the old cert in their queries until they "
"fetch and update the new cert. Likewise, it would allow one to prime the "
"new cert/key without distributing the new cert yet, this can be useful "
"when using a network of servers using anycast and on which the "
"configuration may not get updated at the exact same time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4114
msgid ""
"By priming the cert, the servers can handle both old and new certs "
"traffic while distributing only one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4117
msgid "This option may be specified multiple times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4129
msgid "dnscrypt-shared-secret-cache-size: *<memory size>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4122
msgid ""
"Give the size of the data structure in which the shared secret keys are "
"kept in. In bytes or use m(mega), k(kilo), g(giga). The shared secret "
"cache is used when a same client is making multiple queries using the "
"same public key. It saves a substantial amount of CPU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4138
msgid "dnscrypt-shared-secret-cache-slabs: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4134
msgid ""
"Give power of 2 number of slabs, this is used to reduce lock contention "
"in the dnscrypt shared secrets cache. Close to the number of cpus is a "
"fairly good setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4148
msgid "dnscrypt-nonce-cache-size: *<memory size>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4143
msgid ""
"Give the size of the data structure in which the client nonces are kept "
"in. In bytes or use m(mega), k(kilo), g(giga). The nonce cache is used to"
" prevent dnscrypt message replaying. Client nonce should be unique for "
"any pair of client pk/server sk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4157
msgid "dnscrypt-nonce-cache-slabs: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4153
msgid ""
"Give power of 2 number of slabs, this is used to reduce lock contention "
"in the dnscrypt nonce cache. Close to the number of cpus is a fairly good"
" setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4160
msgid "EDNS Client Subnet Module Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4162
msgid ""
"The ECS module must be configured in the :ref:`module-"
"config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` directive, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4174
msgid ""
"If the destination address is allowed in the configuration Unbound will "
"add the EDNS0 option to the query containing the relevant part of the "
"client's address. When an answer contains the ECS option the response and"
" the option are placed in a specialized cache. If the authority indicated"
" no support, the response is stored in the regular cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4181
msgid ""
"Additionally, when a client includes the option in its queries, Unbound "
"will forward the option when sending the query to addresses that are "
"explicitly allowed in the configuration using :ref:`send-client-"
"subnet:<unbound.conf.ecs.send-client-subnet>`. The option will always be "
"forwarded, regardless the allowed addresses, when :ref:`client-subnet-"
"always-forward: yes<unbound.conf.ecs.client-subnet-always-forward>`. In "
"this case the lookup in the regular cache is skipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4190
msgid ""
"The maximum size of the ECS cache is controlled by :ref:`msg-cache-"
"size:<unbound.conf.msg-cache-size>` in the configuration file. On top of "
"that, for each query only 100 different subnets are allowed to be stored "
"for each address family. Exceeding that number, older entries will be "
"purged from cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4196
msgid ""
"This module does not interact with the :ref:`serve-"
"expired\\*:<unbound.conf.serve-expired>` and "
":ref:`prefetch:<unbound.conf.prefetch>` options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4209
msgid "send-client-subnet: *<IP address>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4203
msgid ""
"Send client source address to this authority. Append /num to indicate a "
"classless delegation netblock, for example like ``10.2.3.4/24`` or "
"``2001::11/64``. Can be given multiple times. Authorities not listed will"
" not receive edns-subnet information, unless domain in query is specified"
" in :ref:`client-subnet-zone:<unbound.conf.ecs.client-subnet-zone>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4218
msgid "client-subnet-zone: *<domain>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4214
msgid ""
"Send client source address in queries for this domain and its subdomains."
" Can be given multiple times. Zones not listed will not receive edns-"
"subnet information, unless hosted by authority specified in :ref:`send-"
"client-subnet:<unbound.conf.ecs.send-client-subnet>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4232
msgid "client-subnet-always-forward: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4223
msgid ""
"Specify whether the ECS address check (configured using :ref:`send-"
"client-subnet:<unbound.conf.ecs.send-client-subnet>`) is applied for all "
"queries, even if the triggering query contains an ECS record, or only for"
" queries for which the ECS record is generated using the querier address "
"(and therefore did not contain ECS data in the client query). If enabled,"
" the address check is skipped when the client query contains an ECS "
"record. And the lookup in the regular cache is skipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4240
msgid "max-client-subnet-ipv6: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4237
msgid ""
"Specifies the maximum prefix length of the client source address we are "
"willing to expose to third parties for IPv6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4240
msgid "Default: 56"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4248
msgid "max-client-subnet-ipv4: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4245
msgid ""
"Specifies the maximum prefix length of the client source address we are "
"willing to expose to third parties for IPv4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4248
msgid "Default: 24"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4258
msgid "min-client-subnet-ipv6: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4253
msgid ""
"Specifies the minimum prefix length of the IPv6 source mask we are "
"willing to accept in queries. Shorter source masks result in REFUSED "
"answers. Source mask of 0 is always accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4267
msgid "min-client-subnet-ipv4: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4263
msgid ""
"Specifies the minimum prefix length of the IPv4 source mask we are "
"willing to accept in queries. Shorter source masks result in REFUSED "
"answers. Source mask of 0 is always accepted. Default: 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4276
msgid "max-ecs-tree-size-ipv4: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4272
#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4281
msgid ""
"Specifies the maximum number of subnets ECS answers kept in the ECS radix"
" tree. This number applies for each qname/qclass/qtype tuple."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4285
msgid "max-ecs-tree-size-ipv6: *<number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4288
msgid "Opportunistic IPsec Support Module Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4290
msgid ""
"The IPsec module must be configured in the :ref:`module-"
"config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` directive, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4297
msgid "and be compiled into Unbound by using ``--enable-ipsecmod`` to be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4303
msgid ""
"When Unbound receives an A/AAAA query that is not in the cache and finds "
"a valid answer, it will withhold returning the answer and instead will "
"generate an IPSECKEY subquery for the same domain name. If an answer was "
"found, Unbound will call an external hook passing the following "
"arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4311
msgid "QNAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4310
msgid "Domain name of the A/AAAA and IPSECKEY query. In string format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4314
msgid "IPSECKEY TTL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4314
msgid "TTL of the IPSECKEY RRset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4318
msgid "A/AAAA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4317
msgid ""
"String of space separated IP addresses present in the A/AAAA RRset. The "
"IP addresses are in string format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4322
msgid "IPSECKEY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4321
msgid ""
"String of space separated IPSECKEY RDATA present in the IPSECKEY RRset. "
"The IPSECKEY RDATA are in DNS presentation format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4324
msgid ""
"The A/AAAA answer is then cached and returned to the client. If the "
"external hook was called the TTL changes to ensure it doesn't surpass "
":ref:`ipsecmod-max-ttl:<unbound.conf.ipsecmod-max-ttl>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4328
msgid ""
"The same procedure is also followed when :ref:`prefetch: "
"yes<unbound.conf.prefetch>` is used, but the A/AAAA answer is given to "
"the client before the hook is called. :ref:`ipsecmod-max-"
"ttl:<unbound.conf.ipsecmod-max-ttl>` ensures that the A/AAAA answer given"
" from cache is still relevant for opportunistic IPsec."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4343
msgid "ipsecmod-enabled: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4337
msgid ""
"Specifies whether the IPsec module is enabled or not. The IPsec module "
"still needs to be defined in the :ref:`module-config:<unbound.conf"
".module-config>` directive. This option facilitates turning on/off the "
"module without restarting/reloading Unbound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4353
msgid "ipsecmod-hook: *<filename>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4348
msgid ""
"Specifies the external hook that Unbound will call with *system(3)*. The "
"file can be specified as an absolute/relative path. The file needs the "
"proper permissions to be able to be executed by the same user that runs "
"Unbound. It must be present when the IPsec module is defined in the :ref"
":`module-config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` directive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4363
msgid "ipsecmod-strict: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4358
msgid ""
"If enabled Unbound requires the external hook to return a success value "
"of 0. Failing to do so Unbound will reply with SERVFAIL. The A/AAAA "
"answer will also not be cached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4371
msgid "ipsecmod-max-ttl: *<seconds>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4368
msgid ""
"Time to live maximum for A/AAAA cached records after calling the external"
" hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4383
msgid "ipsecmod-ignore-bogus: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4376
msgid ""
"Specifies the behaviour of Unbound when the IPSECKEY answer is bogus. If "
"set to yes, the hook will be called and the A/AAAA answer will be "
"returned to the client. If set to no, the hook will not be called and the"
" answer to the A/AAAA query will be SERVFAIL. Mainly used for testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4392
msgid "ipsecmod-allow: *<domain>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4388
msgid ""
"Allow the IPsec module functionality for the domain so that the module "
"logic will be executed. Can be given multiple times, for different "
"domains. If the option is not specified, all domains are treated as being"
" allowed (default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4397
msgid "ipsecmod-whitelist: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4397
msgid "Alternate syntax for :ref:`ipsecmod-allow:<unbound.conf.ipsecmod-allow>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4400
msgid "Cache DB Module Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4402
msgid ""
"The Cache DB module must be configured in the :ref:`module-"
"config:<unbound.conf.module-config>` directive, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4409
msgid "and be compiled into the daemon with ``--enable-cachedb``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4411
msgid ""
"If this module is enabled and configured, the specified backend database "
"works as a second level cache; when Unbound cannot find an answer to a "
"query in its built-in in-memory cache, it consults the specified backend."
" If it finds a valid answer in the backend, Unbound uses it to respond to"
" the query without performing iterative DNS resolution. If Unbound cannot"
" even find an answer in the backend, it resolves the query as usual, and "
"stores the answer in the backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4419
msgid ""
"This module interacts with the *serve-expired-\\** options and will reply"
" with expired data if Unbound is configured for that. Currently the use "
"of :ref:`serve-expired-client-timeout:<unbound.conf.serve-expired-client-"
"timeout>` and :ref:`serve-expired-reply-ttl:<unbound.conf.serve-expired-"
"reply-ttl>` is not consistent for data originating from the external "
"cache as these will result in a reply with 0 TTL without trying to update"
" the data first, ignoring the configured values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4428
msgid ""
"If Unbound was built with ``--with-libhiredis`` on a system that has "
"installed the hiredis C client library of Redis, then the ``redis`` "
"backend can be used. This backend communicates with the specified Redis "
"server over a TCP connection to store and retrieve cache data. It can be "
"used as a persistent and/or shared cache backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4435
msgid ""
"Unbound never removes data stored in the Redis server, even if some data "
"have expired in terms of DNS TTL or the Redis server has cached too much "
"data; if necessary the Redis server must be configured to limit the cache"
" size, preferably with some kind of least-recently-used eviction policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4440
msgid ""
"Additionally, the :ref:`redis-expire-records:<unbound.conf.cachedb.redis-"
"expire-records>` option can be used in order to set the relative DNS TTL "
"of the message as timeout to the Redis records; keep in mind that some "
"additional memory is used per key and that the expire information is "
"stored as absolute Unix timestamps in Redis (computer time must be "
"stable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4447
msgid ""
"This backend uses synchronous communication with the Redis server based "
"on the assumption that the communication is stable and sufficiently fast."
" The thread waiting for a response from the Redis server cannot handle "
"other DNS queries. Although the backend has the ability to reconnect to "
"the server when the connection is closed unexpectedly and there is a "
"configurable timeout in case the server is overly slow or hangs up, these"
" cases are assumed to be very rare. If connection close or timeout "
"happens too often, Unbound will be effectively unusable with this "
"backend. It's the administrator's responsibility to make the assumption "
"hold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4458
msgid "The **cachedb:** clause gives custom settings of the cache DB module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4469
msgid "backend: *<backend name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4463
msgid ""
"Specify the backend database name. The default database is the in-memory "
"backend named ``testframe``, which, as the name suggests, is not of any "
"practical use. Depending on the build-time configuration, ``redis`` "
"backend may also be used as described above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4469
msgid "Default: testframe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4481
msgid "secret-seed: *\"<secret string>\"*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4474
msgid ""
"Specify a seed to calculate a hash value from query information. This "
"value will be used as the key of the corresponding answer for the backend"
" database and can be customized if the hash should not be predictable "
"operationally. If the backend database is shared by multiple Unbound "
"instances, all instances must use the same secret seed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4481
msgid "Default: \"default\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4488
msgid "cachedb-no-store: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4484
msgid ""
"If the backend should be read from, but not written to. This makes this "
"instance not store dns messages in the backend. But if data is available "
"it is retrieved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4490
msgid "The following **cachedb:** options are specific to the ``redis`` backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4500
msgid "redis-server-host: *<server address or name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4495
msgid ""
"The IP (either v6 or v4) address or domain name of the Redis server. In "
"general an IP address should be specified as otherwise Unbound will have "
"to resolve the name of the server every time it establishes a connection "
"to the server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4500
msgid "Default: 127.0.0.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4507
msgid "redis-server-port: *<port number>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4505
msgid "The TCP port number of the Redis server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4507
msgid "Default: 6379"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4515
msgid "redis-server-path: *<unix socket path>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4512
msgid ""
"The unix socket path to connect to the redis server. Unix sockets may "
"have better throughput than the IP address option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4523
msgid "redis-server-password: *\"<password>\"*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4520
msgid ""
"The Redis AUTH password to use for the redis server. Only relevant if "
"Redis is configured for client password authorisation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4533
msgid "redis-timeout: *<msec>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4528
msgid ""
"The period until when Unbound waits for a response from the Redis sever. "
"If this timeout expires Unbound closes the connection, treats it as if "
"the Redis server does not have the requested data, and will try to re-"
"establish a new connection later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4549
msgid "redis-expire-records: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4538
msgid ""
"If Redis record expiration is enabled. If yes, Unbound sets timeout for "
"Redis records so that Redis can evict keys that have expired "
"automatically. If Unbound is configured with :ref:`serve-"
"expired:<unbound.conf.serve-expired>` and :ref:`serve-expired-ttl: "
"0<unbound.conf.serve-expired-ttl>`, this option is internally reverted to"
" \"no\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4547
msgid "Redis SETEX support is required for this option (Redis >= 2.0.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4563
msgid "redis-logical-db: *<logical database index>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4554
msgid ""
"The logical database in Redis to use. These are databases in the same "
"Redis instance sharing the same configuration and persisted in the same "
"RDB/AOF file. If unsure about using this option, Redis documentation "
"(https://redis.io/commands/select/) suggests not to use a single Redis "
"instance for multiple unrelated applications. The default database in "
"Redis is 0 while other logical databases need to be explicitly SELECT'ed "
"upon connecting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4566
msgid "DNSTAP Logging Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4568
msgid ""
"DNSTAP support, when compiled in by using ``--enable-dnstap``, is enabled"
" in the **dnstap:** section. This starts an extra thread (when compiled "
"with threading) that writes the log information to the destination. If "
"Unbound is compiled without threading it does not spawn a thread, but "
"connects per-process to the destination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4583
msgid "dnstap-enable: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4578
msgid ""
"If dnstap is enabled. If yes, it connects to the DNSTAP server and if any"
" of the *dnstap-log-..-messages:* options is enabled it sends logs for "
"those messages to the server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4590
msgid "dnstap-bidirectional: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4588
msgid "Use frame streams in bidirectional mode to transfer DNSTAP messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4598
msgid "dnstap-socket-path: *<file name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4595
msgid ""
"Sets the unix socket file name for connecting to the server that is "
"listening on that socket."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4606
msgid "dnstap-ip: *<IPaddress[@port]>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4603
msgid ""
"If ``\"\"``, the unix socket is used, if set with an IP address (IPv4 or "
"IPv6) that address is used to connect to the server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4615
msgid "dnstap-tls: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4611
msgid ""
"Set this to use TLS to connect to the server specified in :ref:`dnstap-"
"ip:<unbound.conf.dnstap.dnstap-ip>`. If set to no, TCP is used to connect"
" to the server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4624
msgid "dnstap-tls-server-name: *<name of TLS authentication>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4620
msgid ""
"The TLS server name to authenticate the server with. Used when :ref"
":`dnstap-tls: yes<unbound.conf.dnstap.dnstap-tls>`. If ``\"\"`` it is "
"ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4633
msgid "dnstap-tls-cert-bundle: *<file name of cert bundle>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4629
msgid ""
"The pem file with certs to verify the TLS server certificate. If ``\"\"``"
" the server default cert bundle is used, or the windows cert bundle on "
"windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4641
msgid "dnstap-tls-client-key-file: *<file name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4638
msgid ""
"The client key file for TLS client authentication. If ``\"\"`` client "
"authentication is not used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4648
msgid "dnstap-tls-client-cert-file: *<file name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4646
msgid "The client cert file for TLS client authentication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4655
msgid "dnstap-send-identity: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4653
msgid "If enabled, the server identity is included in the log messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4662
msgid "dnstap-send-version: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4660
msgid "If enabled, the server version if included in the log messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4669
msgid "dnstap-identity: *<string>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4667
msgid "The identity to send with messages, if ``\"\"`` the hostname is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4676
msgid "dnstap-version: *<string>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4674
msgid ""
"The version to send with messages, if ``\"\"`` the package version is "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4684
msgid "dnstap-log-resolver-query-messages: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4681
msgid ""
"Enable to log resolver query messages. These are messages from Unbound to"
" upstream servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4692
msgid "dnstap-log-resolver-response-messages: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4689
msgid ""
"Enable to log resolver response messages. These are replies from upstream"
" servers to Unbound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4700
msgid "dnstap-log-client-query-messages: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4697
msgid "Enable to log client query messages. These are client queries to Unbound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4708
msgid "dnstap-log-client-response-messages: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4705
msgid ""
"Enable to log client response messages. These are responses from Unbound "
"to clients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4715
msgid "dnstap-log-forwarder-query-messages: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4713
msgid "Enable to log forwarder query messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4722
msgid "dnstap-log-forwarder-response-messages: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4720
msgid "Enable to log forwarder response messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4727
msgid "Response Policy Zone Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4729
msgid ""
"Response Policy Zones are configured with **rpz:**, and each one must "
"have a :ref:`name:<unbound.conf.rpz.name>`. There can be multiple ones, "
"by listing multiple rpz clauses, each with a different name. RPZ clauses "
"are applied in order of configuration. The respip module needs to be "
"added to the :ref:`module-config<unbound.conf.module-config>`, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4741
msgid ""
"QNAME, Response IP Address, nsdname, nsip and clientip triggers are "
"supported. Supported actions are: NXDOMAIN, NODATA, PASSTHRU, DROP, Local"
" Data, tcp-only and drop. RPZ QNAME triggers are applied after any :ref"
":`local-zone:<unbound.conf.local-zone>` and before any :ref:`auth-"
"zone:<unbound.conf.auth>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4748
msgid ""
"The RPZ zone is formatted with a SOA start record as usual. The items in "
"the zone are entries, that specify what to act on (the trigger) and what "
"to do (the action). The trigger to act on is recorded in the name, the "
"action to do is recorded as the resource record. The names all end in the"
" zone name, so you could type the trigger names without a trailing dot in"
" the zonefile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4756
msgid "An example RPZ record, that answers ``example.com`` with ``NXDOMAIN``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4762
msgid "The triggers are encoded in the name on the left"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4772
msgid ""
"The netblock is written as ``<netblocklen>.<ip address in reverse>``. For"
" IPv6 use ``'zz'`` for ``'::'``. Specify individual addresses with scope "
"length of 32 or 128. For example, ``24.10.100.51.198.rpz-ip`` is "
"``198.51.100.10/24`` and ``32.10.zz.db8.2001.rpz-ip`` is "
"``2001:db8:0:0:0:0:0:10/32``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4778
msgid "The actions are specified with the record on the right"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4789
msgid ""
"Other records like AAAA, TXT and other CNAMEs (not rpz-..) can also be "
"used to answer queries with that content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4792
msgid ""
"The RPZ zones can be configured in the config file with these settings in"
" the **rpz:** block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4813
msgid ""
"If you combine the ``'@'`` and ``'#'``, the ``'@'`` comes first. If you "
"point it at another Unbound instance, it would not work because that does"
" not support AXFR/IXFR for the zone, but if you used "
":ref:`url:<unbound.conf.rpz.url>` to download the zonefile as a text file"
" from a webserver that would work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4826
msgid "Alternate syntax for :ref:`primary:<unbound.conf.rpz.primary>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4849
msgid "url: *<url to zonefile>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4841
msgid ""
"If only urls are given the SOA refresh timer is used to wait for making "
"new downloads. If also primaries are listed, the primaries are first "
"probed with UDP SOA queries to see if the SOA serial number has changed, "
"reducing the number of downloads. If none of the URLs work, the primaries"
" are tried with IXFR and AXFR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4866
msgid "allow-notify: *<IP address or host name or netblockIP / prefix>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4854
msgid ""
"With :ref:`allow-notify:<unbound.conf.rpz.allow-notify>` you can specify "
"additional sources of notifies. When notified, the server attempts to "
"first probe and then zone transfer. If the notify is from a primary, it "
"first attempts that primary. Otherwise other primaries are attempted. If "
"there are no primaries, but only urls, the file is downloaded when "
"notified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4864
msgid ""
"The primaries from :ref:`primary:<unbound.conf.rpz.primary>` and "
":ref:`url:<unbound.conf.rpz.url>` statements are allowed notify by "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4881
msgid "rpz-action-override: *<action>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4879
msgid ""
"Always use this RPZ action for matching triggers from this zone. Possible"
" actions are: *nxdomain*, *nodata*, *passthru*, *drop*, *disabled* and "
"*cname*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4887
msgid "rpz-cname-override: *<domain>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4886
msgid ""
"The CNAME target domain to use if the cname action is configured for :ref"
":`rpz-action-override:<unbound.conf.rpz.rpz-action-override>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4894
msgid "rpz-log: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4892
msgid "Log all applied RPZ actions for this RPZ zone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4899
msgid "rpz-log-name: *<name>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4899
msgid "Specify a string to be part of the log line, for easy referencing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4909
msgid "rpz-signal-nxdomain-ra: *<yes or no>*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4904
msgid ""
"Signal when a query is blocked by the RPZ with NXDOMAIN with an unset RA "
"flag. This allows certain clients, like dnsmasq, to infer that the domain"
" is externally blocked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4914
msgid ""
"If enabled the zone is authoritatively answered for and queries for the "
"RPZ zone information are answered to downstream clients. This is useful "
"for monitoring scripts, that can then access the SOA information to check"
" if the RPZ information is up to date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4933
msgid "tags: *\"<list of tags>\"*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4924
msgid "Limit the policies from this RPZ clause to clients with a matching tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4926
msgid ""
"Tags need to be defined in :ref:`define-tag:<unbound.conf.define-tag>` "
"and can be assigned to client addresses using :ref:`access-control-"
"tag:<unbound.conf.access-control-tag>` or :ref:`interface-"
"tag:<unbound.conf.interface-tag>`. Enclose list of tags in quotes "
"(``\"\"``) and put spaces between tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manpages/unbound.conf.rst:4932
msgid ""
"If no tags are specified the policies from this clause will be applied "
"for all clients."
msgstr ""

